This was the absolute worst experience I’ve ever had at a bar or restaurant. I came to underdog with some friends for after work drinks on January 4th. We were drinking & catching up & our server (a woman with short hair and glasses) seemed in a rush to get us out of there. It wasn’t busy or anything so I didn’t know why. However, one of my friends had to leave so he asked for his check. She ended up bringing everyone’s check even though the rest of us weren’t ready to leave but we all ended up just paying anyway. We paid & we were still sitting down talking and she comes over to us with a very angry temperament and asks if we dissatisfied with the service. We said no. She said “then why wasn’t a gratuity left on the bill? It’s already so hard being a server so for you to not leave a tip is extremely frustrating.” My friend then proceeds say that we were going to leave cash. She then says “I don’t see it on the table!” And I said well we aren’t leaving yet, we’re still sitting here (Two of us weren’t planning on leaving yet because another friend was meeting us there). She then says “it’s fine I just won’t come back around to serve you guys since you don’t want to tip!” I was in complete shock that she was talking to us in that way, especially because we had all intentions of leaving a tip!! She just didn’t give us a chance to. I then asked the bartender if there was a manager around & he said that they just left & I said ok I’ll just come back another day when they’re here. So I went back to the table to sit back down. He then came over to the table to ask what was wrong, seeing that we were upset. I  was explaining to him what happened & the server came up behind him & said “he’s not a manager or anything so don’t think that by complaining to him anything is going to happen.” I was completely shocked by her hostility towards us & it was really unlike anything I’ve ever experienced at a bar or restaurant. I’m really unsure why she felt as though she could speak to paying customers like that but it’s extremely unacceptable. I will never come back to Underdog & i will make sure to tell everyone that I know to not go to Underdog as well. I will also be reaching out to management to get some sort of explanation for her actions and horrible treatment of my friends and I.
